## Quick Reference - Anti-patterns

| Anti-pattern                                    | Why                               | Fix                                        |
| ----------------------------------------------- | --------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------ |
| `it('should return ok')`                        | "should" tense - BetterSpecs rule | `it('returns ok')`                         |
| `beforeEach` in core test                       | core tests need no setup          | use `factory.build()` per test             |
| `factory.create()` in core test                 | `create()` is async and hits DB   | use `factory.build()`                      |
| Multiple `expect` in core `it`                  | hides which assertion fails       | one `expect` per `it`                      |
| `context('invalid title')`                      | missing `when`/`with`/`without`   | `context('when title is empty')`           |
| 10 identical `it` blocks                        | should be a table                 | use `it.each`                              |
| Hand-written object literal when factory exists | inconsistency, drift              | use `factory.build()`                      |
| `describe('task helpers')`                      | vague, not self-documenting       | `describe('src/core/task/task.domain.ts')` |
| Mutation not tested                             | core contract is immutability     | always add `not.toBe(original)` test       |
| Only happy path tested                          | BetterSpecs: test all cases       | add error + edge cases                     |
